pal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Mautby","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from either of two places called Maltby (South Yorkshire, Lincolnshire) or Maltby le Marsh (Lincolnshire); possibly occasionally from Maltby (North Yorkshire) or Mautby (Norfolk). The placenames derive from the Old Norse personal name <i>Malti</i> + Old Norse <i>bȳ</i> ‘farmstead, village’."],"variants":[{"name":"Maltbie","meanings":["Probably an altered form of   Maltby  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Mautby was born about 1300, in Flegg, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, John de Mautby, was 61 and his mother, Elizabeth Clavering, was 31. He had at least 2 sons with Ellen Marshal. He died in Smallburgh, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1300–":"umbes 1300–Surnud","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1325–1403":"1325–1403","1305–Female":"1305–Surnud","1308–Female":"1308–Surnud","1339–1374":"1339–1374","1325–1370":"1325–1370","1345–1374":"1345–1374","1240–1336":"1240–1336","1270–1329":"1270–1329","about 9 January 1339":"umbes 9. jaanuar 1339","1374":"1374","Bef 1325":"enne 1325","1240":"1240","Abt 1345":"umbes 1345","1370":"1370","1270":"1270","1305":"1305","1403":"1403","1336":"1336","1325":"1325","Abt 1300":"umbes 1300","1345":"1345","1300":"1300","1308":"1308","1329":"1329","1339":"1339","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","Flegg, Norfolk, England":"Flegg, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Smallburgh, Norfolk, England":"Smallburgh, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1300–":"noin 1300–Kuollut","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1325–1403":"1325–1403","1305–Female":"1305–Kuollut","1308–Female":"1308–Kuollut","1339–1374":"1339–1374","1325–1370":"1325–1370","1345–1374":"1345–1374","1240–1336":"1240–1336","1270–1329":"1270–1329","about 9 January 1339":"noin 9. tammikuuta 1339","1374":"1374","Bef 1325":"ennen vuotta 1325","1240":"1240","Abt 1345":"noin 1345","1370":"1370","1270":"1270","1305":"1305","1403":"1403","1336":"1336","1325":"1325","Abt 1300":"noin 1300","1345":"1345","1300":"1300","1308":"1308","1329":"1329","1339":"1339","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","Flegg, Norfolk, England":"Flegg, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Smallburgh, Norfolk, England":"Smallburgh, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1300–":"environ 1300–Décédé","1300–Male":"1300–Décédé","1325–1403":"1325–1403","1305–Female":"1305–Décédée","1308–Fem